@@yThe Northern Pyramid@@N

@@eThe Northern Pyramid is the ascendant state-monument of the Sand Sovereign,
a dynastic heir who claimed descent from the Solar Court's Dawn Liturgists.
It was built not merely as a tomb but as a political machine in stone, its
ascending floors encoding a doctrine of celestial legitimacy.@@N

@@dThe Sand Sovereign hired oasis-trained engineers from the Great Oasis
Measuring House, inheriting the Keepers of Measure's obsession with precision.
Astronomical alignment chambers replicate the Measuring House's gnomon
corridors at monumental scale, each calibration passage measuring celestial
positions through angular methodology the Keepers pioneered.@@N

@@yThe charter road system that connects the Great Oasis to the pyramid is not
a wilderness track but a surveyed spur of the Keeper-era road network. Charter
stones mark distance, toll rates, and legal witness seals. The last mile
widens into processional architecture where toll marks shift from water-debt
notation to tribute language, marking the point where trade law became
theology.@@N

@@eThe pyramid's seven ascending floors bind seven guardian spirits in a
military-funerary hierarchy, from the Crypt Pharaoh in the undercroft to the
Sand Sovereign's self-bound spirit at the apex. The binding mathematics were
borrowed from the Great Pyramid's Seal College, containment geometry designed
for a far more dangerous purpose, repurposed as spirit-binding lattices.@@N

@@rThis hidden purpose is the pyramid's deepest secret: it was designed as a
backup containment ring for the Great Pyramid. Should the Black Sun Shard's
seals fail, the guardian floors would absorb and disperse anti-light radiation.
The apex summit is oriented toward the Great Pyramid on the horizon, creating
a resonance channel between the two structures.@@N

@@dInscriptions reference 'the elder court' and 'the disk that does not set,'
oblique claims to Solar Court legitimacy that carefully avoid acknowledging
the Great Pyramid's superiority.@@N
